//http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4686543/sql-query-to-concatenate-column-values-from-multiple-rows-in-oracle
// SQL Query to concatenate column values from multiple rows

#input

| PID |
|-----|
| A   |
| B   |
| C   |

#input

PID,   SEQ ,   Descr
A  ,   1   ,   Have
A  ,   2   ,   a nice
A  ,   3   ,   day.
B  ,   1   ,   Nice Work.
C  ,   1   ,   Yes
C  ,   2   ,   we can 
C  ,   3   ,   do 
C  ,   4   ,   this work!

#output

PID,   Descr
A  ,   Have a nice day.
B  ,   Nice Work.
C  ,   Yes we can do this work!

#constraint
{
	"constants": [],
	"aggregation_functions": ["concat"]
}

#solution

```sql
SELECT
    T0.PID,
    string_agg(T1.Descr, ' ') 
FROM
    input1 AS T0 
JOIN
    input2 AS T1 
        ON T0.PID = T1.PID 
GROUP BY
    T0.PID 
ORDER BY
    T0.PID ASC
```
